  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Green Belt Sixth and Fifth Gup The color green represents the plants which grow deep roots and begin to tower over the land. It is a time of sturdiness, growth, and reliability. Green is also the first intermediate color, and signifies that the basics of white and yellow can now be utilized. The Green Belt Student is further introduced to the principles of the energy of water, and learns the fundamentals of flow. Green Belt Curriculum Introduction Form (Attitude) One-Steps GB 1–3 Techniques High Green Belt Curriculum Form (Waterfall) One-Steps GB 4–6 Techniques Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
